# Test Documentation Rules

## docs/TEST-PLAN.md

This is the single source of truth for all tests. It must be kept in sync with the actual test files.

## When Adding Tests

Every time a new test is added, you MUST:
1. Add a row to the relevant table in `docs/TEST-PLAN.md` with: file name, test name, what it validates.
2. Update the "Test Coverage Summary" totals at the bottom.
3. Update the "Last updated" date.

## When Removing or Modifying Tests

1. Update or remove the corresponding row in the test plan table.
2. Update coverage totals.
3. Update the "Last updated" date.

## Table Format

```markdown
| Test File | Test Name | What It Validates |
|-----------|-----------|-------------------|
| `file.spec.ts` | descriptive test name | Brief validation description |
```
